p style="margin-left: 40px;">Chapter 3: Project integration management</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Chapter 4: Project scope management</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Chapter 5: Project time management</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Chapter 6: Project cost management</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Chapter 7: Project quality management</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Chapter 8: Project human resource management</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Chapter 9: Project communication management</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Chapter 10: Project risk management</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Chapter 11: Project procurement management</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 40px;">Chapter 12: Project stakeholder management</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center; "><em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 22px; text-align: center; ">Access blog of project management training&nbsp;<a href="http://www.stevbros.com/project-management-training/" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 141, 183); text-decoration: none; ">here</a>!</em></p>\r\n', '2013-03-06 00:00:00', '2013-03-06 02:54:48', 0, 'Project Management Body of Knowledge Course', 0, 'vi', ',4,16,', 'admin', 'phuong', 0),
(6, 'Accelerated PMP® Exam Preparation', 'accelerated-pmp-exam-prep-course', 'accelerated-pmp®-exam-prep-course.jpg', '2-day workshop + 20-hour e-learning. For anyone planning to take PMP® exam. This directed study course is designed to prepare you for the PMP® exam in effective manner with a minimum amount of studying after class!', '<p><span style="color:#B22222;"><strong>Duration: 2-day workshop + 20-hour e-learning, earn 35 PDUs.</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Who should attend: For anyone planning to take PMP<span style="font-size: 13px; ">®</span> exam. This directed study course is designed to prepare you for the PMP<span style="font-size: 13px; ">®</span> exam in effective manner with a minimum amount of studying!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img alt="Accelerated PMP Exam Workshop effectively" src="/public/images/articles/stevbros-project-management-in-house-training.jpg" style="opacity: 0.9; font-size: 13px; text-align: center; width: 600px; height: 279px;" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>After the course, you will</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Identify gaps in your knowledge that may hurt you on the exam</li>\r\n	<li>Be more comfortable with the types of questions you will see on the exam</li>\r\n	<li>Utilize your personalized test taking strategy</li>\r\n	<li>Apply project management techniques useful in the real world</li>\r\n	<li>Be a better project manager</li>\r\n	<li>Earn certificate of 35 PDUs</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Accelerated PMP Exam Workshop effectively" src="/public/images/articles/accelerated-pmp%C2%AE-exam-prep-course(2).jpg" style="opacity: 0.9; font-size: 13px; text-align: center; width: 600px; height: 204px;" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Content: </strong>this is blended training course including</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px;"><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.6em;">Workshop (2 days): Accelerated PMP</span><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.6em;">® Exam Prep</span></li>\r\n	<li style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px;">E-learning after the workshop (20&nbsp;hours in 2 months): Practise 5 mock tests&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Information of PMP® certificate:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To apply for the PMP®, you need to have either:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A secondary degree (high school diploma, associate’s degree, or the global equivalent) with at least five years of project management experience, with 7,500 hours leading and directing projects and 35 hours of project management education. OR</li>\r\n	<li>A four-year degree (bachelor’s degree or the global equivalent) and at least three years of project management experience, with 4,500 hours leading and directing projects and 35 hours of project management education.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center; "><em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 22px; text-align: center; ">Access blog of project management training&nbsp;<a href="http://www.stevbros.com/project-management-training/" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 141, 183); text-decoration: none; ">here</a>!</em></p>\r\n', '2013-03-06 00:00:00', '2014-05-08 00:41:45', 1, 'Accelerated PMP® Exam Preparation  Course', 0, 'vi', ',4,16,', 'admin', 'phuong', 0),
(7, 'Project Management Competency Assessment', 'project-management-competency-assessment', 'danh-gia-nang-luc.jpg', 'Stevbros provides a project management competency assessment framework for determining, measuring, and supporting the improvement of an individuals’ performance in project management.', '<h2>Stevbros provides a project management competency assessment framework for determining, measuring, and supporting the improvement of an individuals’ performance in project management. The assessment result is also used to discover where additional training is needed, and develop training roadmaps for project managers.</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center; "><img alt="" src="/public/images/articles/pmbok-10-knowledge-areas.jpg" style="width: 500px; height: 485px;" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center; "><em>Project Manager Knowledge Competence</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Project management assessment framework evaluates 3 dimensions of competence: Project Manager Knowledge Competence, Project Manager Performance Competence and Project Manager Personal Competence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center; "><img alt="" src="/public/images/articles/danhgianangluc2.jpg" style="width: 500px; height: 366px; " /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center; "><i>Project Manager Performance Competence</i></p>\r\n\r\n<div class="page" title="Page 17">\r\n<div class="layoutArea">\r\n<div class="column">\r\n<p>Knowledge competence is what the project manager knows about the application of project management processes and their tools and techniques for project activities. <span style="font-size: 13px;">Knowledge competence comprises of 10&nbsp;units</span>:&nbsp;projects scope management, project time management, project cost management, project quality management, project communications management, project risk management, project human resource management, project procurement management, project stakeholder management, project integration management.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 22px;"><img alt="" src="/public/images/articles/pmcd-personal-competencies.jpg" style="width: 500px; height: 512px;" /></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Project Manager Personal Competence</em></p>\r\n\r\n<div class="page" title="Page 18">\r\n<div class="layoutArea">\r\n<div class="column">\r\n<p>Performance competence is what the project manager is able to do or accomplish by applying their project management knowledge. Performance competence comprises of 5 units:&nbsp;initiating a project, planning a project, executing a project, monitoring and controlling a project, and closing a project.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Personal competencies are personal ability of project managers applied to lead project team, engage project stakeholders and manage project activities effectively. Personal competencies are grouped into 6 units: communicating, leading, managing, cognitive ability, effectiveness, and professionalism.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '2013-03-06 00:00:00', '2013-07-01 19:27:36', 1, 'Project Management Competency Assessment', 0, 'vi', ',5,', 'admin', 'phuong', 0),
