(37, 'How to pass PMP® certification exam for sure', 'how-to-pass-pmp-certification-exam-for-sure', 'pass-PMP-certification-exam-for-sure.jpg', 'People normally google tips and tricks to pass for sure when preparing for their exams, especially for the exams of professional certificates. The following are 5 things that can help you pass PMP® certification exam for sure.', '<h2><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">People normally google tips and tricks to pass for sure when preparing for their exams, especially for the exams of professional certificates. The following are 5 things that can help you pass PMP</span>®<span style="line-height: 1.6em;"> certification exam for sure.</span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><img alt="How to pass PMP® certification exam for sure" src="/public/images/articles/pass-PMP-certification-exam-for-sure.jpg" style="width: 500px; height: 445px;" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;">1)&nbsp;&nbsp; Self-draw table of 47 processes in the lasted edition of PMBOK</span>: draw the table in page 61 of PMBOK 5<sup>th</sup> edition by yourself. It will help you quickly identify what process group or what knowledge area a certain process belong to in the <strong>PMP® certification exam.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="line-height: 1.6em;"><span style="font-size:20px;">2)&nbsp;&nbsp; Compose a checklist of concepts, formulas, terms, rules of thumbs</span>: understand all concepts in project management framework, know how to apply formulas (e.g. formulas of EVM, project selection methods, communication channel), understand all terms and know how a certain term is applied in a situation (in this case, the term become the keyword to help you answer the situation question), and remember all rules of thumbs (or heuristics) in the practice of project management.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;">3)&nbsp;&nbsp; Read the lasted edition of PMBOK carefully</span>: it is not easy to remember all Inputs, Tools and Techniques, Outputs (ITTOs) of 47 processes. However, you should remember key ITTOs and purpose of each process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;">4)&nbsp;&nbsp; Practise quizzes and score no less than 80%</span>: <a href="http://www.stevbros.com/project-management-training/pmp-exam-prep-35-pdus-lowest-price.html">practise questions for review</a> in all chapters of PMBOK 5<sup>th</sup> edition and <a href="http://www.stevbros.com/project-management-training/pmp-mock-tests-simulating-the-real-pmp-exam.html">take some mock tests</a> if possible. Most of&nbsp;online systems allow you to practice quizzes many times, so that you should try to score no less than 80% before to take the real <strong>PMP® certification exam</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:20px;">5)&nbsp;&nbsp; Build your own hints to answer situation questions</span>: besides situation questions related to terms, there are many situation questions related to professionalism. Professionalism means to conform to an ethical behavior governed by responsibility, respect, fairness and honesty in the practice of project management. It can be easy at the first look on this kind of question, but it quickly gets complicated after you read&nbsp;whole situation. You must practice to build your own hints to answer this kind of question correctly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.stevbros.com/payment/pmp-exam-prep-35-pdus-lowest-price.html"><img alt="How to pass PMP® certification exam for sure" src="/public/images/articles/PMP-Exam-Prep-Online-35-PDU-lowest-price.jpg" style="width: 599px; height: 345px;" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 22px; text-align: center;"><em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px;">PMP® exam preparation 35 PDUs. Price $35.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;